programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Volunteers
programme.desc: A group of Resistance capture a volunteer from a Taelon program for youth. Liam decides they may learn valuable information from her. They also decide to send in one of their own as a volunteer to see what the program is teaching.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Bliss
programme.desc: Lili is given a psychotropic drug called "bliss" via a Taelon device. They discover it is widespread. With an instantly strong addictive property, the addicts are dying within 48 hours. The investigation leads Liam and Sandoval to Ireland.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Highjacked
programme.desc: With a reporter on board, the Taelon mother ship is highjacked into interdimensional space. Liam is the prime suspect, causing an even bigger rift between Da'an and Zo'or. As the ship floats, lost in space, they must find the real culprit.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Defector
programme.desc: A shuttle crashes on a beach after being pursued by a second Taelon piloted shuttle. When Liam locates the survivor (a Taelon called Belleye), he claims to want to help the Resistance take back Earth from the Taelons.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Heroes and Heartbreak
programme.desc: Augur is recruited by a Taelon weapons project, but the others are worried about his involvement. When the project is launched earlier than originally planned to fight a Jiridian fleet, the Earth is in danger.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Message in a Bottle
programme.desc: A Jiridian probe headed for Earth is shot down by the Taelon Embassy and crashes outside of D.C. Liam recovers the probe, but he, Augur, and Julia are captured by another underground resistance movement led by the real Colonel Liam Kincaid.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Crossfire
programme.desc: As the election draws near, Liam believes Zo'or is trying to have Jonathan Doors murdered. The Resistance worries that an attack is imminent at the final debate. Julia mobilizes a group to protect Doors against Liam's wishes.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Crackdown
programme.desc: An unknown woman saves Augur and Liam from the raids on the Resistance. Lili sabotages the mother ship, but Zo'or stops its total destruction. Lili is reportedly dead. The investigation on the President's shooter continues.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Vanished
programme.desc: Some who were detained during the Resistance sweep have not reappeared after their release. Lili is taken to a lab run by Sandoval and implanted. Renee tries to help Liam find the missing people.

programme.title: Divorce Court: Alpha Girl

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Anniversary

programme.title: Paranormal State: Ghosts of the Forgotten
programme.desc: The PRS investigation into the haunted Lake County Poor House becomes a journey through one PRS team members? troubled past.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Desperate Households
programme.desc: When Julie and her family moved into their dream home in suburban New Jersey they quickly realized they were not alone.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Connection
programme.desc: P.R.S. is called in to help a young mother tormented by an otherworldly connection to a teenage girl murdered in her neighborhood years ago. Could she have psychic ability or is there a more sinister force at work?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Church of the Damned
programme.desc: Jason and his family can no longer do renovations of an abandoned Kansas church, especially after they found their father in the basement crying and frightened because of the menacing activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Who Is the Lurking Man?
programme.desc: PRS travels to Newcastle, CA to investigate a house with paranormal forces so strong, the family has cleared out. Ryan believes the Native American land may hold the key to the mystery and leads the team in a fight to reclaim a scared family's house.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Suicide Possession
programme.desc: Joan and her boyfriend Tony are seeing apparitions in their New Jersey home. Both are concerned that the spirits are influencing their behavior: a non-drinker, Tony has turned to the bottle while Joan has thoughts of harming herself.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Hostage to Fear
programme.desc: P.R.S. is summoned to help a family who has been haunted for years by spirits lurking in the house. Upon arrival the team finds a family that has become prisoners in their own home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Man of the House
programme.desc: PRS is called to help a grandmother and her frightened grandson when renovations on her 19th century house stir up the pipe-smoking specter of a former tenant named Alfred.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Bedroom Eyes
programme.desc: PRS travels to rural Pennsylvania to investigate a haunting that began after a new couple moved into an old family farm.?Over the next three days, hidden tragedies are uncovered and latent psychic abilities are revealed.

programme.title: Paranormal State: School House Haunting

programme.title: Most Haunted: Charnock Hall

programme.title: Most Haunted: Culzean Castle
programme.desc: Culzean Castle in Ayrshire, Scotland is supposed to be haunted by seven ghosts. Derek arrives and takes the crew straight to the most haunted room in the house, the Earl of Cassillis's bedroom.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Mermaid Inn
programme.desc: The ghosts of smugglers terrify the crew when they spend 24 hours at the Mermaid Inn. A haunted chair moves on its own and reports of ghostly men fighting a duel a bedrooms spur the team on.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Blackpool Pleasure Beach
programme.desc: The team spends 24 hours at Blackpool's famous funfair to investigate a haunted ghost train and poltergeist activity. Derek sees ghostly children in the gift shop and phantom footsteps are heard.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Treasure Holt House
programme.desc: Stories of witchcraft, murder and human sacrifice bring the team to Treasure Holt. Derek is guided by the spirit of a monk and contacts two of the ghosts seen in what was once a house of disrepute.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Derby Gaol
programme.desc: Historian Richard Felix joins Yvette and the team as they are locked inside Derby Gaol, where scenes of total incarceration and brutal executions have taken place since 1756.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Aldwych Underground Station
programme.desc: Yvette and Jason dress up in 1940s army uniforms as they investigate Aldwych Station, which was built after demolishing a theatre in 1907, and used as an air raid shelter during WWII.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Charleville Forest Castle
programme.desc: Located in the center of Ireland, Charleville Forest Castle is built on the site of an ancient burial ground where plague victims were buried in the 1700s. The team holds a Victorian-style séance.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Michelam Priory
programme.desc: Michelam Priory was originally a church built on a medieval moated island. In 1556 it was transformed into a house where many families have lived through history and tragedy.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Brannigans Nightclub, Manchester
programme.desc: The team investigates reports of considerable poltergeist activity and spectral sighting. They encounter two entities that did not want a television crew in the building, according to Derek.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tutbury Castle, Staffordshire
programme.desc: Tutbury is an ancient castle steeped in bloody history, which once held Mary, Queen of Scots. During their 24-hour vigil, the team hopes to encounter a ghostly lady and meet historian Lesley Smith.

programme.desc: An estranged daughter is writing a vengeful expose about her mother, a much-beloved movie star.

programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark visit a halfway house for people who were confined to mental facilities but released because they were deemed no longer a danger to society.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Hero

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Parents' Day
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark work as police detectives in a school. Their assignment: to investigate drug selling.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Father's Faith
programme.desc: A fisherman's livelihood is in jeopardy because of the amount of time he devotes to his comatose son.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Heavy Date
programme.desc: A young man learns that the girl he's in love with is pregnant.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Ghost Rider
programme.desc: A lonely spy-story writer buys her murdered hero's sports car, which comes complete with his ghost.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Debbie Vercoe

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Janice Holmes "One Year On"
programme.desc: A year ago wife and mother, Janice Holmes was 42 but the poll of one hundred people in her hometown of Blackpool put their average guess at six years older than she really is. Nicky Hambleton-Jones revisits one year on.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting the Ball in Her Court
programme.desc: Kristin is an aspiring television sportscaster, but her appearance is getting in the way of landing her dream job. But our team is on the ball and is hoping to get Kristin ready for air!
programme.sub-title: Getting the Ball in Her Court

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Gill Collyer
programme.desc: A hectic household of 3 lively kids, 1 husband, 4 cats and a dog, equals chaos and stress for Gill Collyer from Devon and it's showing all over her face. Luckily Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team are here to the rescue.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Father To Son
programme.desc: Tobe took a hiatus from his career to care for his dying father, and now he's trying to pick up where he left off. Tobe needs to refurbish his appearance so he can look like the man his younger wife married.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Dawn Of A New Day
programme.desc: Dawn Peluso is a stay at home mother of three. Taking care of her children is a full time job – one that doesn't allow personal pamper breaks. Dawn is afraid her looks are going out with the dirty diapers, and she is concerned for her marriage.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Wendy Grace
programme.desc: Ex glamour model and air hostess Wendy Grace lost her good looks when she gave up that life for a market stall in Christchurch. Hair, make up and a new wardrobe will all help in the fight to make Wendy look younger but her face needs urgent repair work.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Knockout Makeover
programme.desc: As a former title holding boxer and stuntwoman, Bridgett spent years getting pummeled and abused and her looks are now suffering. We're going to unleash Bridgett's feminine flair and make her look 10 years younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Diamond in the Rough
programme.desc: Dashia is a spinning instructor by day and a feisty tenants rights advocate in her spare time. Our Glam Squad and team of doctors are going to take this diamond in the rough and smooth out some of the sharp edges.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hope for the Best
programme.desc: Hope is a dedicated single parent who has been told she dresses too old for her age. Along with the daily stresses of work and motherhood, the recent loss of Hope's mother's has also taken its toll on her appearance.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Felicia Gets Her Groove Back
programme.desc: After the death of both her mother and boyfriend, Felicia is trying to get back her zest for life. She has surrendered to the experts on hand to help her jump back into her old self. Will she rebound for a slam-dunk makeover?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Standing Up To Her Past
programme.desc: Norma Jean is a single, working mother of two whom by night makes audiences laugh as a stand-up comic, but worries that her tired and worn down appearance may be what they're laughing at instead.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Debbie Ashcroft
programme.desc: 46 year old Debbie Ashcroft is a lifelong smoker and sunbed addict with the peculiar habit of bleaching her hair up to six times a week. Can the expect team make Debbie look 10 years younger?
